The '''School of Physics''' is a constituent body of the [[Sydney Faculty of Science|Faculty of Science]] at the [[University of Sydney]], [[Australia]].
==History== Physics was first taught at the tertiary level in Australia at the University of Sydney, beginning in 1852.<ref>http://www.physics.usyd.edu.au/about/history.shtml</ref> After the establishment of the [[Sydney Faculty of Science|Faculty of Science]] in 1882, the School was established as a distinct entity within the Faculty.
